WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:05.045
[projector whirring]

00:11.553 --> 00:14.555
[tinkling]

00:33.408 --> 00:36.410
[insects chirping,
clock ticking]

00:39.956 --> 00:42.958
[eerie music]

00:42.959 --> 00:50.966
♪ ♪

01:17.952 --> 01:20.954
[clock ticking,
insects chirping]

01:23.917 --> 01:24.917
[glass breaks]

01:24.918 --> 01:27.503
- [gasps]

01:27.504 --> 01:30.506
[squeaking in distance]

01:32.133 --> 01:34.301
Richard. Richard.

01:34.302 --> 01:35.427
- Yeah?

01:35.428 --> 01:37.554
- I think I heard something.

01:39.224 --> 01:40.557
[creaking in distance]

01:40.558 --> 01:42.184
[soft tap]

01:44.521 --> 01:45.604
[rustling]

01:45.605 --> 01:47.272
[gasps]

01:47.273 --> 01:50.275
[suspenseful music]

01:50.276 --> 01:55.114
♪ ♪

01:55.115 --> 01:58.117
- [breathing heavily]

02:14.134 --> 02:15.467
[whispers]
Stay here.

02:18.012 --> 02:21.014
[clock ticking]

02:27.397 --> 02:31.066
- [snoring softly]

02:31.067 --> 02:32.526
[floorboard creaks]

02:37.407 --> 02:40.409
[floorboards creaking]

02:41.995 --> 02:44.621
[clock ticking]

02:44.622 --> 02:46.373
[light clicking]

02:59.179 --> 03:01.305
[floorboard creaks]

03:13.484 --> 03:14.860
[gun cocks]

03:18.323 --> 03:19.364
[clock chiming]

03:19.365 --> 03:20.866
[gunshot]

03:20.867 --> 03:22.534
- [exhales sharply]

03:22.535 --> 03:25.704
[breathing heavily]

03:38.343 --> 03:39.676
- Richard?
- God...

03:39.677 --> 03:40.802
- Ah!
[gasps]

03:40.803 --> 03:43.055
- Damn it.

03:43.056 --> 03:45.265
[exhales sharply]

03:45.266 --> 03:48.268
[breathing heavily]

03:52.440 --> 03:54.858
[groaning]

03:56.986 --> 03:59.238
[gun thuds]

03:59.239 --> 04:02.699
- [gasping]

04:05.203 --> 04:06.411
[groans]

04:06.412 --> 04:09.414
- [breathing heavily]

04:09.415 --> 04:12.417
[sirens wailing]

04:20.510 --> 04:23.512
[camera shutter clicks]

04:25.223 --> 04:26.682
- How you feeling, son?

04:26.683 --> 04:28.684
[indistinct police radio
chatter]

04:28.685 --> 04:31.353
- Peachy, aside from almost
shitting myself.

04:31.354 --> 04:33.188
- Yeah, must have been
a scary thing

04:33.189 --> 04:34.856
for a man like you.

04:36.776 --> 04:38.777
A civilian, I mean.

04:40.113 --> 04:42.489
His name was, uh,
Freddy Russel.

04:43.366 --> 04:45.325
- You know him?

04:45.326 --> 04:47.494
- I know shit
when I step in it.

04:47.495 --> 04:49.579
I'm gonna have to ask you
to come down to the station,

04:49.580 --> 04:51.748
make out a formal statement,
okay?

04:53.459 --> 04:55.544
[indistinct police radio
chatter]

04:55.545 --> 04:56.920
- [exhales sharply]

04:56.921 --> 04:59.006
[car doors thudding]

05:03.928 --> 05:06.930
[foreboding music]

05:06.931 --> 05:14.938
♪ ♪

05:28.578 --> 05:31.580
[typewriter keys clacking]

05:37.086 --> 05:39.296
- Okay.

05:40.465 --> 05:42.591
- Now what?

05:42.592 --> 05:44.760
- It'll go to the grand jury.

05:44.761 --> 05:46.178
They'll look over
your statement,

05:46.179 --> 05:50.015
your wife's, mine,
and they'll nobill you.

05:50.016 --> 05:51.391
- What about the courts?

05:51.392 --> 05:53.310
- It'll never get that far.

05:53.311 --> 05:55.062
It was self-defense.

05:55.063 --> 05:56.396
- He was unarmed.

05:56.397 --> 05:58.607
- Well, you didn't know that.

05:58.608 --> 06:00.233
It's called "fear of life."

06:00.234 --> 06:02.277
Uh, legally,

06:02.278 --> 06:05.530
he might as well have been
pointing a gun at you.

06:05.531 --> 06:07.366
Look...

06:07.367 --> 06:09.117
He's a wanted felon.

06:09.118 --> 06:13.121
You're an upstanding citizen
without a record.

06:13.122 --> 06:14.623
Sometimes the good guy wins.

06:14.624 --> 06:16.208
- Hmm.

06:16.209 --> 06:18.877
- We're gonna have to keep that
awhile, okay?

06:19.962 --> 06:22.631
- Belonged to my dad.

06:22.632 --> 06:23.840
- He was a good man.

06:23.841 --> 06:26.134
He'd have been proud.

06:26.135 --> 06:28.929
- [exhales sharply]

06:28.930 --> 06:31.640
Of what?
My finger slipped.

06:36.062 --> 06:39.064
[door creaking]

06:41.192 --> 06:42.234
[door thuds]

06:45.321 --> 06:46.988
[grunts]

06:48.991 --> 06:52.327
[insects chirping]

06:53.496 --> 06:54.746
[sighs]

06:54.747 --> 06:56.540
- You okay?

06:59.293 --> 07:00.961
- Uh-uh.

07:04.715 --> 07:10.220
- ♪ As I prepare ♪

07:10.221 --> 07:12.013
♪ To lay down ♪

07:12.014 --> 07:16.101
♪ Here alone, dear ♪

07:16.102 --> 07:18.687
♪ I can't help ♪

07:18.688 --> 07:20.605
♪ But to keep wishing ♪

07:20.606 --> 07:23.692
♪ That you were here ♪

07:23.693 --> 07:24.901
[jazzy music]

07:24.902 --> 07:27.237
♪ I done you wrong ♪

07:27.238 --> 07:29.906
♪ But now you are gone ♪

07:29.907 --> 07:32.617
♪ What can I do now? ♪

07:32.618 --> 07:34.077
♪ ♪

07:34.078 --> 07:35.954
♪ Don't make me live ♪

07:35.955 --> 07:38.373
♪ The rest of my life ♪

07:38.374 --> 07:40.792
♪ Forgetting you now ♪

07:40.793 --> 07:43.003
♪ ♪

07:43.004 --> 07:45.380
♪ It's too bad ♪

07:45.381 --> 07:47.215
♪ I didn't realize ♪

07:47.216 --> 07:49.968
♪ Until you were gone ♪

07:49.969 --> 07:51.136
♪ ♪

07:51.137 --> 07:53.138
♪ Just what it meant ♪

07:53.139 --> 07:54.639
♪ ♪

07:54.640 --> 07:56.099
♪ To have a love like you ♪

07:56.100 --> 07:59.060
♪ For my own ♪

07:59.061 --> 08:00.145
♪ ♪

08:00.146 --> 08:02.147
♪ But now that you've gone ♪

08:02.148 --> 08:04.649
♪ I know I can't go on ♪

08:04.650 --> 08:07.611
♪ Living here without you now ♪

08:07.612 --> 08:08.987
♪ ♪

08:08.988 --> 08:10.906
♪ Don't make me live ♪

08:10.907 --> 08:12.657
♪ The rest of my life ♪

08:12.658 --> 08:13.658
- [sighs]

08:13.659 --> 08:15.952
- ♪ Forgetting you now ♪

08:15.953 --> 08:17.162
♪ Oh, now ♪

08:17.163 --> 08:19.206
- Come on, bud.
Let's go back to bed.

08:19.207 --> 08:21.791
♪ ♪

08:21.792 --> 08:23.126
[grunts]

08:23.127 --> 08:24.711
- ♪ It will be so hard,
I know ♪

08:24.712 --> 08:25.754
♪ ♪

08:25.755 --> 08:27.255
♪ But listen, baby ♪

08:27.256 --> 08:30.258
[birds chirping]

08:33.179 --> 08:36.181
- Jordan, son, stop jiggling.

08:38.100 --> 08:40.769
Now, you can't take that
to school with you.

08:40.770 --> 08:42.812
- Why?
- Just because.

08:42.813 --> 08:43.813
- Because why?

08:43.813 --> 08:46.316
- Because I'm your father
and I said so.

08:50.279 --> 08:51.696
- Bang!
- Hey.

08:51.697 --> 08:53.365
- You dead!

08:53.366 --> 08:54.449
[toy gun clatters]

08:54.450 --> 08:56.368
- Don't you say that to me.

08:57.870 --> 08:59.204
I don't want to snap at you,
son,

08:59.205 --> 09:00.539
but I don't like that game.

09:03.084 --> 09:04.960
Come on.
Let's go.

09:09.006 --> 09:11.341
[horn honks]

09:12.343 --> 09:14.135
[bicycle bell rings]

09:16.681 --> 09:19.683
[birds chirping]

09:21.227 --> 09:22.811
[telephone ringing]

09:22.812 --> 09:25.188
[door creaks,
bell tinkles]

09:29.443 --> 09:31.903
- Dane's Frames.

09:31.904 --> 09:34.030
For you, Mr. Dane.

09:36.450 --> 09:37.742
Morning.

09:37.743 --> 09:39.077
- Morning.

09:39.078 --> 09:40.161
Hello?

09:40.162 --> 09:41.830
- It's me.

09:43.124 --> 09:44.291
- Just a minute.

09:44.292 --> 09:45.292
- Richard...

09:45.293 --> 09:47.252
it's all over the school.

09:47.253 --> 09:50.213
The students keep asking me
about it.

09:50.214 --> 09:51.423
- [sighs]

09:51.424 --> 09:52.674
Shit.

09:52.675 --> 09:54.009
Maybe you should go home.

09:54.010 --> 09:55.051
- I can't.

09:55.052 --> 09:56.136
[bell rings]

09:56.137 --> 09:58.096
I have to talk
with the police later.

09:59.515 --> 10:00.724
- What the hell for?

10:00.725 --> 10:02.892
- Uh...
I don't know.

10:02.893 --> 10:04.769
They... they want a statement
from me.

10:04.770 --> 10:06.896
- [sighs]

10:07.690 --> 10:09.774
- How are you feeling?

10:14.280 --> 10:15.447
- Fine.

10:16.741 --> 10:19.618
- I'll see you later tonight,
okay?

10:19.619 --> 10:21.286
[line clicks and buzzes]

10:21.287 --> 10:22.287
[sighs]

10:22.288 --> 10:23.872
[door creaks and bell tinkles]

10:23.873 --> 10:25.582
- Oh, man.

10:25.583 --> 10:27.000
That air conditioner
feels good.

10:27.001 --> 10:28.251
[door thuds, bell tinkles]

10:28.252 --> 10:29.294
Whew.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.212
I hear you got you one
last night.

10:32.089 --> 10:33.715
Back at the paper, they told me.

10:33.716 --> 10:37.135
I couldn't believe it was you
at first.

10:37.136 --> 10:38.678
I didn't think
you had it in you.

10:38.679 --> 10:39.804
- Hey, take it easy, Jack.

10:39.805 --> 10:41.139
It's not something I'm proud of.

10:41.140 --> 10:43.141
- Well, it's nothing
to be ashamed of.

10:43.142 --> 10:45.143
Some son of a bitch
breaks into my house,

10:45.144 --> 10:47.771
he better be ready to pick
his teeth out of his ass.

10:47.772 --> 10:49.481
Shoot, man, if it was me...

10:49.482 --> 10:50.523
- It wasn't you.

10:50.524 --> 10:52.233
It was me.

10:52.234 --> 10:53.902
Now, Jack, if you got mail,
leave it.

10:53.903 --> 10:55.570
Otherwise, I'm busy.

10:55.571 --> 10:56.821
[twangy music playing]

10:56.822 --> 10:58.615
[bell dings]

10:58.616 --> 10:59.699
- Here you go, y'all.

10:59.700 --> 11:01.409
Y'all need anything else
right now?

11:01.410 --> 11:03.828
[indistinct conversations]

11:03.829 --> 11:05.580
[door rattles]

11:05.581 --> 11:07.582
[conversations stop]

11:07.583 --> 11:09.167
- ♪ When that world ♪

11:09.168 --> 11:10.794
♪ ♪

11:10.795 --> 11:13.254
♪ Has walked on me ♪

11:13.255 --> 11:14.798
- Uh, beer.

11:16.133 --> 11:17.884
- Little early, isn't it?

11:17.885 --> 11:18.968
- Not today.

11:18.969 --> 11:21.304
- ♪ If there's not ♪

11:21.305 --> 11:22.305
- [exhales sharply]

11:22.306 --> 11:23.473
- ♪ Enough money ♪

11:23.474 --> 11:24.557
♪ ♪

11:24.558 --> 11:26.601
♪ Well, she smiles ♪

11:26.602 --> 11:27.644
♪ ♪

11:27.645 --> 11:28.770
♪ That's all right ♪

11:28.771 --> 11:29.813
- Right this way.

11:29.814 --> 11:30.814
- [sighs]

11:30.815 --> 11:33.233
- ♪ Tells me that's ♪

11:33.234 --> 11:36.277
♪ What your woman ♪

11:36.278 --> 11:38.071
♪ Is for ♪

11:38.072 --> 11:40.573
♪ ♪

11:40.574 --> 11:41.741
- Howdy, Rich.

11:43.035 --> 11:44.703
How you feeling?

11:44.704 --> 11:45.745
- [sighs]

11:45.746 --> 11:47.497
[scoffs]

11:47.498 --> 11:48.832
Like a bucket of shit.

11:48.833 --> 11:50.208
- Shake it off.

11:54.255 --> 11:55.505
- So what happens now?

11:56.340 --> 11:58.383
- We bury the son of a bitch.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.051
- ♪ Only me ♪

12:00.052 --> 12:01.094
- When?

12:01.095 --> 12:02.137
- Tomorrow,

12:02.138 --> 12:04.013
noon, Greenley's Cemetery,

12:04.014 --> 12:06.182
courtesy of the county.

12:07.476 --> 12:08.977
- He got any family?

12:08.978 --> 12:10.437
- He got a daddy

12:10.438 --> 12:11.855
in Huntsville Prison.

12:11.856 --> 12:14.065
He just got paroled.

12:14.066 --> 12:15.859
Shit don't fall
far from the tree.

12:15.860 --> 12:17.402
[hand taps]

12:17.403 --> 12:18.737
- ♪ She tells me that's... ♪

12:18.738 --> 12:21.823
♪ ♪

12:21.824 --> 12:24.826
[machine whirring and grinding]

12:31.208 --> 12:33.418
- And I can get these
installed today?

12:33.419 --> 12:35.670
- Mm.

12:56.901 --> 12:59.903
[light scraping]

13:12.249 --> 13:14.250
[door thuds]

13:17.296 --> 13:18.588
- Ted.

13:18.589 --> 13:20.924
- Hey, Rich.

13:20.925 --> 13:22.967
We'll be out of your hair
in a little while.

13:22.968 --> 13:24.677
[foot slams]

13:33.479 --> 13:34.646
- That couch looks hideous.

13:34.647 --> 13:36.105
- We can take it back.

13:36.106 --> 13:38.191
- I thought we agreed
on the floral theme.

13:38.192 --> 13:39.526
- I made a decision.
I'm sorry.

13:39.527 --> 13:40.819
I didn't think
it was a big deal.

13:40.820 --> 13:42.695
- I thought we made
these decisions together.

13:42.696 --> 13:44.656
- Can we talk about something
besides the couch?

13:44.657 --> 13:45.824
- Okay.

13:45.825 --> 13:46.866
[telephones ringing]

13:46.867 --> 13:48.868
Did you see the locksmith bill?

13:48.869 --> 13:50.829
- [sighs]

13:50.830 --> 13:52.330
[footsteps tapping]

13:52.331 --> 13:53.373
[sighs]

13:53.374 --> 13:54.707
[ringing continues]

13:54.708 --> 13:56.709
- You've reached
the Dane residence.

13:56.710 --> 13:59.337
Please leave your name
after the beep.

13:59.338 --> 14:01.172
Thank you, and God bless.

14:01.173 --> 14:02.674
[answering machine beeps]

14:02.675 --> 14:06.302
[static hissing]

14:17.189 --> 14:18.189
[line clicks and buzzes]

14:18.190 --> 14:19.983
[answering machine beeps]

14:19.984 --> 14:22.360
[sighs]

14:26.115 --> 14:29.117
[answering machine whirring]

14:31.370 --> 14:32.495
[answering machine clicks]

14:32.496 --> 14:34.122
[birds chirping]

14:34.123 --> 14:35.748
[answering machine clicks]

14:37.042 --> 14:40.044
[suspenseful music]

14:40.045 --> 14:43.172
♪ ♪

14:43.173 --> 14:44.424
[insects chirping]

14:44.425 --> 14:45.925
- [sighs]

14:47.970 --> 14:49.637
[moans]

14:53.350 --> 14:55.393
[grunts lightly]

14:55.394 --> 15:03.192
♪ ♪

15:03.193 --> 15:05.194
[engine droning]

15:05.195 --> 15:08.197
- [breathing heavily]

15:09.491 --> 15:12.493
[engine revving]

15:12.494 --> 15:20.501
♪ ♪

15:32.932 --> 15:34.891
[zipper clicking]

15:34.892 --> 15:36.893
- Here, looking for the base.

15:36.894 --> 15:39.896
- [breathes deeply]

15:41.148 --> 15:43.733
- Called safe
by the first base umpire.

15:44.735 --> 15:45.944
Got to try to catch him late...

15:45.945 --> 15:48.613
I guess he ran that
all the way.

15:48.614 --> 15:50.281
[cheers and applause]

15:50.282 --> 15:51.824
One and two...

15:51.825 --> 15:54.827
[speaking indistinctly]

15:54.828 --> 15:55.870
Outside...

15:55.871 --> 15:57.497
- [inhales deeply]

15:57.498 --> 16:00.917
[exhales]

16:00.918 --> 16:03.920
[bell tolling]

16:21.146 --> 16:23.564
[gravel scrapes]

16:25.109 --> 16:28.111
[tolling continues]

16:32.116 --> 16:35.118
- [speaking indistinctly]

16:42.501 --> 16:43.584
Amen.

16:43.585 --> 16:46.254
[speaking indistinctly]

16:49.925 --> 16:51.926
[keys jangle]

16:51.927 --> 16:55.263
[shovels scraping]

17:00.561 --> 17:03.855
[indistinct conversation]

17:07.233 --> 17:10.069
[wings fluttering]

17:10.069 --> 17:12.864
[cow moos]

17:12.865 --> 17:14.323
[scraping continues]

17:14.324 --> 17:17.160
- So we got to get here
at 6:00 in the morning...

17:17.161 --> 17:18.994
- I am not getting here
at 6:00 in the morning...

17:21.205 --> 17:22.874
- Quiet and peaceful,
isn't it?

17:25.627 --> 17:28.629
[crows cawing]

17:31.633 --> 17:32.800
You're, uh,

17:32.801 --> 17:34.886
Dane, right?

17:37.806 --> 17:39.891
Come to watch the shit
go in the hole?

17:39.892 --> 17:41.726
[lighter clicks]

17:41.727 --> 17:43.394
Very Christian of you.

17:46.023 --> 17:48.191
[shovels scraping]

17:49.568 --> 17:51.611
- I'm sure this doesn't make it
any better for you,

17:51.612 --> 17:55.073
Mr. Russel,
but I'm sorry for what happened.

17:55.074 --> 17:57.617
He didn't give me much choice.

18:03.707 --> 18:05.708
- Yeah.

18:05.709 --> 18:08.044
You're right.

18:08.045 --> 18:10.922
Doesn't make it any better.

18:14.718 --> 18:18.179
Oh, that was a nice picture
of your family in the paper.

18:18.180 --> 18:20.014
[scraping continues]

18:20.015 --> 18:22.058
Your boy...

18:22.059 --> 18:24.602
he looks a whole lot like you,
doesn't he?

18:24.603 --> 18:26.854
[lighter clicking]

18:28.774 --> 18:30.900
Now, you have a nice day now,
you hear?

18:30.901 --> 18:33.903
[dramatic music]

18:33.904 --> 18:37.240
- [exhales sharply]

18:37.241 --> 18:39.784
[engine turns over]

18:39.785 --> 18:47.792
♪ ♪

18:51.964 --> 18:53.965
Yeah, it's Richard.
Is she free?

18:55.008 --> 18:56.134
Well... yeah, okay.

18:56.135 --> 18:57.176
Tell her not to worry

18:57.177 --> 18:59.971
but to meet me
at the police station.

18:59.972 --> 19:02.974
No, everything's fine.

19:02.975 --> 19:05.893
[children shouting indistinctly]

19:18.407 --> 19:20.158
- Jordan, your dad's here.

19:20.159 --> 19:21.325
[laughter]

19:21.326 --> 19:23.578
Come on back.
- Jordan.

19:23.579 --> 19:25.830
Hey.
Jordan!

19:25.831 --> 19:27.165
Jordan, hey.

19:27.166 --> 19:28.666
Come on. Come on.

19:28.667 --> 19:29.834
Come with me right now.

19:29.835 --> 19:31.127
We're going.
Come with me.

19:31.128 --> 19:32.837
We're going.
Get in the car.

19:32.838 --> 19:34.422
Come on, son.
Son, come on.

19:34.423 --> 19:36.465
Get in the car.

19:37.843 --> 19:39.844
[breathing heavily]

19:54.610 --> 19:56.819
- Did he say anything to you
at the school?

19:56.820 --> 19:58.154
- No, he just waved.

19:59.573 --> 20:01.199
- He waved?
- Yeah.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.825
[sniffs]

20:02.826 --> 20:04.452
- So what do you want me
to do here, Rich?

20:04.453 --> 20:05.995
- I want him arrested.

20:05.996 --> 20:07.163
- For what?

20:07.164 --> 20:08.539
He hasn't done anything.

20:08.540 --> 20:10.374
- He threatened my son.

20:10.375 --> 20:11.876
- He said your boy
looks like you.

20:11.877 --> 20:12.960
It's not a threat.

20:12.961 --> 20:14.295
- He showed up
at Jordan's school.

20:14.296 --> 20:15.796
- In broad daylight,
in front of witnesses,

20:15.797 --> 20:17.423
and did nothing.

20:17.424 --> 20:18.674
- He wants my son.

20:18.675 --> 20:20.176
I know it.
I want protection.

20:20.177 --> 20:21.219
- That's not gonna happen,

20:21.220 --> 20:22.887
not without a legal reason.

20:23.680 --> 20:25.806
- [scoffs]

20:25.807 --> 20:27.892
- I'll tell you what I'll do,
Rich.

20:27.893 --> 20:30.645
Unofficially, I'll have a car
stop by your house

20:30.646 --> 20:32.897
every couple hours
over the next few days,

20:32.898 --> 20:34.523
give you
a little peace of mind.

20:34.524 --> 20:36.734
He's probably just trying
to scare you.

20:36.735 --> 20:38.736
Don't let him.

20:39.780 --> 20:41.239
- What were you thinking?

20:41.240 --> 20:43.074
Richard.

20:43.075 --> 20:44.242
Why even go there?

20:44.243 --> 20:45.576
- It was a mistake, okay?

20:45.577 --> 20:46.661
I fucked up.

20:46.662 --> 20:47.828
[fork clanks]

20:47.829 --> 20:49.080
- I don't like that word,

20:49.081 --> 20:50.248
not in front of Jordan.

20:52.918 --> 20:54.585
What are we supposed to do now?

20:54.586 --> 20:56.545
- [sighs]

20:56.546 --> 20:58.422
Maybe you and Jordan
should stay at your mom's

20:58.423 --> 20:59.757
for a while
until this blows over.

20:59.758 --> 21:02.051
- What if he follows us there?

21:02.052 --> 21:04.762
I don't want to put her
in danger too.

21:05.764 --> 21:07.723
What about your dad's cabin?

21:07.724 --> 21:09.350
- No, it's too isolated.

21:09.351 --> 21:11.060
Besides, that's the last place
I want to be.

21:11.061 --> 21:13.062
- I want a igloo colada.

21:13.063 --> 21:15.064
- Son, don't talk
when other people are talking.

21:15.065 --> 21:16.107
It's not polite.

21:16.108 --> 21:17.900
Eat your dinner.

21:17.901 --> 21:19.777
I say we stay home,

21:19.778 --> 21:22.405
take Jordan out of school
for a little while,

21:22.406 --> 21:24.448
let the cops handle it.

21:24.449 --> 21:25.616
We wait him out.

21:25.617 --> 21:27.535
We already got bars
on the windows and...

21:27.536 --> 21:29.287
- But I don't want...
- Damn it, Jordan!

21:29.288 --> 21:32.290
[cup clatters]

21:36.461 --> 21:39.255
[cup clatters]

21:40.465 --> 21:43.634
[indistinct conversations]

21:43.635 --> 21:46.262
[twangy music playing]

21:46.263 --> 21:48.681
- ♪ I'll be here ♪

21:48.682 --> 21:52.310
[singing indistinctly]

21:52.311 --> 21:53.978
♪ ♪

21:53.979 --> 21:56.147
[keys jangle]

22:01.236 --> 22:04.238
[engine turns over]

22:06.491 --> 22:08.284
- [sighs]

22:09.911 --> 22:12.330
[sighs]

22:23.592 --> 22:25.968
[exhales sharply]

22:34.269 --> 22:35.770
[car door thuds]

22:41.526 --> 22:42.610
Get back in the car.

22:42.611 --> 22:44.278
- What?

22:44.279 --> 22:46.197
- The lock's busted.

22:46.198 --> 22:47.531
- Oh, my God.

22:47.532 --> 22:49.408
- Go to the Fergusons'
and call the police.

22:49.409 --> 22:50.785
Ask for Price.

22:50.786 --> 22:52.453
- What are you doing?

22:53.705 --> 22:55.831
Aren't you coming with us?

22:55.832 --> 22:58.084
Richard, get in the car.
- Ann, get, now.

22:58.085 --> 22:59.168
- Come with us.

22:59.169 --> 23:00.378
- I said go.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.213
- Richard, don't be stupid.
- Go, Ann.

23:02.214 --> 23:03.881
[engine turns over]

23:07.719 --> 23:10.721
[dramatic music]

23:10.722 --> 23:18.896
♪ ♪

23:22.234 --> 23:24.777
[door creaking]

23:24.778 --> 23:26.612
[door rattles]

23:26.613 --> 23:29.532
[door creaks and clicks]

23:36.081 --> 23:38.791
[metal creaking]

23:45.173 --> 23:46.549
[metal creaks]

23:52.222 --> 23:55.224
[creaking continues]

24:09.656 --> 24:12.658
[metal creaking]

24:15.787 --> 24:17.163
[breathing heavily]

24:17.164 --> 24:19.415
[metal clinks]

24:29.551 --> 24:31.135
[thunder rumbling]

24:31.136 --> 24:33.637
[sirens wailing]

24:39.644 --> 24:40.978
- Whoever it was

24:40.979 --> 24:43.689
knows his way around
alarm systems.

24:43.690 --> 24:45.399
- We know who it was.

24:45.400 --> 24:47.651
- Excuse me, Detective.

24:50.363 --> 24:52.364
That goes for everybody.

24:53.492 --> 24:55.326
- [sighs]

24:55.327 --> 24:57.161
- I was wrong.

24:57.162 --> 24:58.454
I thought he'd move on,

24:58.455 --> 25:01.999
but at least we have
a reasonable suspicion now.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.418
That means I can give you
official protection.

25:05.754 --> 25:08.589
Now, all you got to do
is be normal...

25:08.590 --> 25:10.257
go to work,
take Jordan to school,

25:10.258 --> 25:11.383
be seen.

25:11.384 --> 25:13.719
And everywhere you go,

25:13.720 --> 25:15.054
I'll have someone watching.

25:15.055 --> 25:17.181
So when he makes his move,

25:17.182 --> 25:19.099
we make our move.

25:20.477 --> 25:22.478
- So we're the bait.

25:22.479 --> 25:24.522
- For want of a better word,
yeah.

25:26.691 --> 25:28.943
- What do you say, Ann?

25:31.738 --> 25:33.989
- Let's nail
that son of a bitch.

25:33.990 --> 25:37.826
[thunder crashes]

25:37.827 --> 25:40.204
[insects chirping]

25:40.205 --> 25:42.122
- I got men
hiding out in the woods.

25:42.123 --> 25:43.415
He sees me drive away,

25:43.416 --> 25:45.000
he's gonna think
you're here all alone.

25:45.001 --> 25:46.377
This is Kevin.

25:46.378 --> 25:47.878
He's a good man,
ex-Special Forces.

25:47.879 --> 25:50.047
Anyone see you come in here?
- Piece of cake.

25:50.048 --> 25:51.799
- Kevin's gonna stay here
with you.

25:51.800 --> 25:53.884
- For how long?

25:53.885 --> 25:55.678
- As long as it takes.

25:57.305 --> 25:58.389
- What do we do?

25:58.390 --> 26:00.015
- You go to bed.
Get some sleep.

26:00.016 --> 26:01.100
You're gonna need it.

26:08.275 --> 26:09.900
- [sighs]

26:13.905 --> 26:16.407
[thunder rumbling]

26:16.408 --> 26:18.534
[locks clicking]

26:19.661 --> 26:22.663
[rain pattering]

26:24.583 --> 26:26.250
[thunder rumbling]

26:28.128 --> 26:31.130
[thunder crashing]

26:39.347 --> 26:41.557
[whispers]
I like him when he's sleeping.

26:42.726 --> 26:44.101
- [whispers]
Yeah.

26:44.102 --> 26:45.769
He's sweet.

26:48.481 --> 26:49.857
[sighs]

27:02.203 --> 27:05.205
[thunder crashing]

27:18.720 --> 27:21.722
[rain pattering]

27:25.518 --> 27:28.270
[thunder rumbling]

27:28.271 --> 27:29.813
- [sighs]

27:31.941 --> 27:32.941
[rain rushing]

27:32.942 --> 27:34.485
- God damn...

27:47.832 --> 27:49.833
[thunder rumbles]

28:03.848 --> 28:04.932
[door creaks]

28:04.933 --> 28:07.309
- [sighs]

28:14.192 --> 28:16.443
[thunder crashes]

