- Ah!

32:30.031 --> 32:32.240
[knocking on door]

32:32.241 --> 32:34.159
- The door's locked.
Somebody go around back.

32:34.160 --> 32:35.243
- [gasping]

32:35.244 --> 32:36.328
- [grunts]

32:36.329 --> 32:38.038
- I can't get it open!
- Open up, Ann!

32:38.039 --> 32:39.206
- [grunting]

32:39.207 --> 32:40.874
[door cracks]

32:42.543 --> 32:43.835
- Jordan!

32:43.836 --> 32:45.629
Jordan!

32:45.630 --> 32:47.005
[grunts]

32:47.006 --> 32:48.048
[thunder crashes]

32:48.049 --> 32:49.383
[grunts]
Oh.

32:50.802 --> 32:52.344
- He's in the woods.
Move. Move.

32:52.345 --> 32:54.554
- Thank God.

32:54.555 --> 32:56.223
Oh!

32:56.224 --> 32:59.226
[gasping]

33:02.563 --> 33:04.731
- [exhales sharply]

33:04.732 --> 33:06.066
- [groans]

33:09.821 --> 33:11.154
- Tracked him
down to the river,

33:11.155 --> 33:12.656
but the rain's making it hard.

33:12.657 --> 33:14.324
- How'd he get in?

33:15.785 --> 33:16.868
- [sighs]

33:16.869 --> 33:18.120
- How'd he get in the house,
Ray?

33:19.247 --> 33:20.414
- He never left.

33:20.415 --> 33:21.957
Son of a bitch
was in the crawl space

33:21.958 --> 33:24.251
the whole time.

33:24.252 --> 33:26.461
- Jesus Christ.

33:28.047 --> 33:29.214
- We'll get him, Rich.

33:30.383 --> 33:32.676
Don't you worry.

33:40.018 --> 33:42.436
- [sighs]

33:42.437 --> 33:44.563
- [whimpers]

33:48.651 --> 33:50.569
[sighs]

33:50.570 --> 33:53.572
[birds chirping]

33:56.242 --> 33:59.244
[alarm clock beeping]

34:06.627 --> 34:08.003
- [grunts]

34:09.547 --> 34:11.339
[sighs]

34:13.634 --> 34:16.636
[footsteps tapping]

34:21.184 --> 34:22.184
[sighs]

34:22.185 --> 34:25.896
[telephones ringing]

34:25.897 --> 34:27.773
[sighs]

34:31.194 --> 34:33.110
Nuevo Laredo?

34:33.112 --> 34:35.155
- Yep, piece of shit
went to Mexico.

34:35.156 --> 34:36.489
- Mexico?

34:36.491 --> 34:38.241
- Federales picked him up
across the border.

34:38.242 --> 34:39.534
We got him, Rich.

34:39.534 --> 34:41.286
Dragging him back to Huntsville
as we speak.

34:41.286 --> 34:44.331
His age, he'll never set foot
in this county again.

34:44.331 --> 34:45.998
Listen, uh,
we just wrapped the paperwork

34:46.000 --> 34:47.000
on the Freddy file.

34:47.001 --> 34:48.251
Why don't you stop down

34:48.252 --> 34:49.585
and we'll close this out
for good?

34:49.587 --> 34:52.047
Then you owe me a beer,
compañero, okay?

34:52.047 --> 34:54.382
- Okay.

34:54.382 --> 34:56.551
[inhales sharply]

34:56.552 --> 34:57.636
[grunts]

34:57.637 --> 35:00.555
[upbeat rock music]

35:00.556 --> 35:02.015
- ♪ Hey ♪

35:02.016 --> 35:10.023
♪ ♪

35:14.112 --> 35:15.737
♪ Looking back... ♪

35:15.738 --> 35:17.572
[singing indistinctly]

35:17.573 --> 35:18.990
[engine shuts off,
music stops]

35:18.991 --> 35:20.992
- [sighs]

35:20.993 --> 35:22.202
- That's it.

35:22.203 --> 35:25.497
Sign these last two,
and you're on your way.

35:25.498 --> 35:26.998
- All right.

35:35.258 --> 35:38.927
[indistinct conversations]

35:38.928 --> 35:40.554
[knocking on desk]

36:08.916 --> 36:10.876
What's this?

36:12.295 --> 36:14.963
It says "Freddy Russell."

36:14.964 --> 36:16.548
- So?

36:16.549 --> 36:18.592
- So that's not the guy
I shot.

36:18.593 --> 36:21.094
Is that some kind of mistake
or what?

36:21.095 --> 36:23.430
[indistinct police radio
chatter]

36:23.431 --> 36:25.807
- That's Freddy Russel.

36:25.808 --> 36:27.976
It's just a bad mug shot,
not very recent.

36:27.977 --> 36:30.145
People change, Rich.

36:31.439 --> 36:32.814
- Well, not that much.

36:32.815 --> 36:35.358
- You were pretty upset
that night, remember?

36:35.359 --> 36:38.653
- Yeah, he died
right in front of me.

36:38.654 --> 36:41.281
I look at pictures of faces
all day.

36:41.282 --> 36:42.949
That is not the guy.

36:46.204 --> 36:48.538
- It's called shock, okay?

36:48.539 --> 36:49.748
Memory gets a little fuzzy.

36:49.749 --> 36:50.832
It happens.

36:50.833 --> 36:52.792
Now, why don't you go home

36:52.793 --> 36:54.836
and let me deal
with the police work, huh?

36:54.837 --> 36:56.171
- [sighs]

36:57.924 --> 36:59.716
- Give my regards to Ann,
huh?

36:59.717 --> 37:02.260
[door rattles]

37:02.261 --> 37:04.095
- [sighs]

37:11.646 --> 37:13.146
[sighs]

37:31.540 --> 37:33.875
[sighs]

37:35.211 --> 37:38.213
[tapping and beeping]

37:39.507 --> 37:42.509
[line ringing]

37:44.595 --> 37:46.763
- Sheriff's offices.
Price here.

37:46.764 --> 37:47.889
- Hey, Ray.

37:47.890 --> 37:50.558
This is Richard Dane.

37:50.559 --> 37:52.143
- What is it, Rich?

37:52.144 --> 37:53.478
- [sighs heavily]

37:53.479 --> 37:55.021
That wanted poster
is bugging me.

37:55.022 --> 37:56.940
It's not him, Ray.

37:56.941 --> 37:58.775
- We've been through this.
It's late. I'm busy.

37:58.776 --> 38:00.652
Give it a rest.

38:00.653 --> 38:01.820
- Well, just hear me out.

38:01.821 --> 38:03.113
- I did, and you're wrong.

38:03.114 --> 38:04.906
Case closed, over.
Now get some sleep.

38:04.907 --> 38:05.907
[line clicks]

38:05.908 --> 38:08.910
[line buzzing]

38:10.371 --> 38:12.080
- [sighs]

38:16.961 --> 38:20.088
[line beeping]

38:20.089 --> 38:22.299
[line ringing]

38:22.300 --> 38:24.676
- Sheriff's office.

38:24.677 --> 38:27.387
- Yeah, Lieutenant Price,
please.

38:28.931 --> 38:30.890
- Sorry.
He's not here, sir.

38:30.891 --> 38:32.392
Can I take a message?

38:32.393 --> 38:34.644
- [exhales sharply]

38:36.772 --> 38:39.774
[engine revving]

38:44.613 --> 38:46.364
[keys jangle]

38:46.365 --> 38:48.616
[engine shuts off]

38:48.617 --> 38:51.036
