[screen door slams]

45:53.083 --> 45:56.085
[door squeaks]

45:56.086 --> 46:03.050
♪ ♪

46:03.051 --> 46:05.136
- [exhales]

46:07.055 --> 46:08.181
- Whoa.

46:08.182 --> 46:09.182
[grunts]

46:10.225 --> 46:12.727
What happened to your shoes?

46:12.728 --> 46:15.146
- Oh.

46:15.147 --> 46:17.482
I drove out and checked
on the cabin yesterday.

46:17.483 --> 46:19.817
Must have stepped in some muck.

46:19.818 --> 46:21.444
- I thought you didn't like
going there.

46:21.445 --> 46:22.612
- Yeah, I know,

46:22.613 --> 46:25.406
but I figured
I got to clean it out sometime.

46:25.407 --> 46:26.491
- And?

46:26.492 --> 46:27.617
- [sighs]

46:27.618 --> 46:29.869
My father
didn't leave much behind.

46:29.870 --> 46:31.746
There you go.

46:31.747 --> 46:33.247
[train horn blaring]

46:33.248 --> 46:36.250
[train rumbling]

46:40.964 --> 46:42.965
[pensive piano music]

46:42.966 --> 46:44.592
[no audible dialogue]

46:44.593 --> 46:52.600
♪ ♪

46:54.436 --> 46:57.438
[bell ringing]

46:57.439 --> 47:00.274
♪ ♪

47:00.275 --> 47:01.317
- Richard?

47:01.318 --> 47:02.401
[ringing stops]

47:02.402 --> 47:05.530
[birds chirping]

47:11.745 --> 47:14.789
[gravel crunching]

47:14.790 --> 47:16.791
[bird tweeting]

47:43.735 --> 47:46.654
[screen door creaks]

47:46.655 --> 47:48.781
[screen door slams]

47:48.782 --> 47:51.784
[birds chirping]

47:57.749 --> 48:00.501
[rustling]

48:15.100 --> 48:17.101
- I didn't kill your son.

48:18.770 --> 48:19.979
- Fuck you.

48:21.481 --> 48:23.357
- Look, I think the cops
have been lying to us both

48:23.358 --> 48:25.526
all along.

48:25.527 --> 48:27.028
- Where's my shoe?

48:31.325 --> 48:32.950
[door rattles]

48:39.499 --> 48:41.459
- The cops
are up to something,

48:41.460 --> 48:42.460
right?

48:42.461 --> 48:44.086
Something to do
with your son,

48:44.087 --> 48:46.255
with you.

48:47.215 --> 48:48.633
Why do they want you dead?

48:48.634 --> 48:49.967
- How should I know?

48:49.968 --> 48:51.719
Same reason you do.

48:51.720 --> 48:54.221
- [sighs]

48:54.222 --> 48:55.389
Look.

48:58.101 --> 48:59.185
Something's going on.

49:00.771 --> 49:03.439
They used my family as bait

49:03.440 --> 49:05.316
to find you.

49:05.317 --> 49:07.109
Now, I want to know why.

49:08.445 --> 49:09.779
- Did you take my lighter?

49:11.782 --> 49:12.949
- No.

49:12.950 --> 49:14.450
- Well, where is it?

49:17.579 --> 49:19.830
- [sighs]

49:24.002 --> 49:27.004
- [gulping]

49:28.548 --> 49:29.715
[sighs]

49:32.552 --> 49:34.470
What's the matter?
You scared?

49:34.471 --> 49:38.140
[laughing]

49:38.141 --> 49:39.433
Huh?

49:40.352 --> 49:44.271
[lighter clicking]

49:44.272 --> 49:46.857
- When's the last time
you heard from your son?

49:49.778 --> 49:52.279
- Oh, it's been
a good long while.

49:53.949 --> 49:56.784
He was about the same age
as your boy.

49:59.955 --> 50:03.457
[lighter clicking]

50:09.423 --> 50:12.800
- [sighs]

50:12.801 --> 50:14.552
I could have left you
on those train tracks,

50:14.553 --> 50:15.678
but I didn't.

50:16.805 --> 50:19.056
I didn't kill your son.

50:19.057 --> 50:20.766
Who you gonna trust,

50:20.767 --> 50:23.769
the cops that just tried
to kill you or me?

50:24.813 --> 50:27.940
- All I know is what I'm told.

50:29.276 --> 50:30.776
[lighter clicks and snaps]

50:30.777 --> 50:33.154
And I'm told
I got nothing left.

50:33.155 --> 50:34.905
- I didn't kill your son.

50:34.906 --> 50:36.490
- So you say.

50:36.491 --> 50:38.784
[lighter clicks and snaps]

50:38.785 --> 50:40.411
- Okay.

50:41.580 --> 50:43.998
You're coming with me.

50:49.004 --> 50:52.965
[thunder rumbling]

50:52.966 --> 50:55.968
[foreboding music]

50:55.969 --> 51:03.976
♪ ♪

51:06.688 --> 51:09.690
[breathing heavily]

51:11.276 --> 51:12.902
- Ah...

51:12.903 --> 51:13.986
- Dig.

51:18.617 --> 51:21.619
[shovel scraping]

51:23.830 --> 51:31.837
♪ ♪

51:34.007 --> 51:36.759
[bird warbles]

51:36.760 --> 51:38.010
[thunder rumbling]

51:38.011 --> 51:41.013
[both grunting]

51:41.014 --> 51:49.021
♪ ♪

52:04.412 --> 52:06.914
[thunder rumbling]

52:06.915 --> 52:08.916
[shovel thuds]

52:11.044 --> 52:13.379
[sighs]

52:13.380 --> 52:15.923
[both grunting]

52:23.598 --> 52:25.975
[panting]

52:25.976 --> 52:28.102
Do it.

52:31.898 --> 52:33.440
[thunder rumbling]

52:36.069 --> 52:39.071
[wood cracking]

52:45.954 --> 52:47.163
[crowbar thuds]

52:57.090 --> 52:59.049
- Ugh. Jeez.
- [gags]

53:01.303 --> 53:04.305
[gagging]

53:08.226 --> 53:10.102
- That ain't him.
That's not Freddy.

53:14.065 --> 53:15.149
[breathes deeply]

53:15.150 --> 53:16.692
[thunder rumbling]

53:16.693 --> 53:18.360
God...

53:21.489 --> 53:23.324
- Jesus.
Who would do that?

53:25.827 --> 53:29.163
- Somebody who didn't want him
identified, ever.

53:29.164 --> 53:32.166
[rain pattering]

53:37.839 --> 53:39.965
Come on.
Get out of there.

53:43.845 --> 53:46.972
[thunder rumbling]

53:46.973 --> 53:49.141
[Jimmie Gray's My World
playing]

53:49.142 --> 53:51.310
- ♪ I'll admit ♪

53:51.311 --> 53:52.394
- [sighs]

53:52.395 --> 53:53.646
- ♪ I've been tempted ♪

53:53.647 --> 53:56.482
♪ But I'm happy to say ♪

53:56.483 --> 53:58.234
- What do we do now?

53:58.235 --> 54:00.152
- We?

54:00.153 --> 54:01.779
[scoffs]

54:01.780 --> 54:03.280
- ♪ In my world ♪

54:03.281 --> 54:04.490
- Yeah.

54:04.491 --> 54:05.699
[twangy music playing]

54:05.700 --> 54:07.993
- ♪ If you look out ♪

54:07.994 --> 54:09.870
♪ Your window ♪

54:09.871 --> 54:13.165
♪ To the bright light below ♪

54:13.166 --> 54:14.291
♪ You can see ♪

54:14.292 --> 54:16.126
- I'll pay you back.

54:16.127 --> 54:20.047
- ♪ It's a temptatious game ♪

54:20.048 --> 54:21.840
♪ ♪

54:21.841 --> 54:26.470
♪ I looked out
of that window ♪

54:26.471 --> 54:29.890
♪ To the bright lights below ♪

54:29.891 --> 54:32.476
♪ And I don't feel ♪

54:32.477 --> 54:34.561
♪ That I've missed ♪

54:34.562 --> 54:36.480
♪ A thing ♪

54:36.481 --> 54:38.524
♪ ♪

54:38.525 --> 54:41.735
♪ Why men can be tempted ♪

54:41.736 --> 54:44.238
- Hey.
Ben.

54:44.239 --> 54:45.656
Russel.

54:45.657 --> 54:46.657
Long time.

54:46.658 --> 54:48.909
- ♪ For a moment ♪

54:48.910 --> 54:51.912
♪ With the wrong kind of girl ♪

54:51.913 --> 54:53.998
- I need some help.

54:53.999 --> 54:55.082
It's about my son.

54:55.083 --> 54:58.836
- ♪ I guess I've been lucky ♪

54:58.837 --> 55:02.381
♪ But I'm happy to see ♪

55:02.382 --> 55:05.217
♪ 'Cause there's a whole lot ♪

55:05.218 --> 55:09.054
♪ Of love in my world ♪

55:09.055 --> 55:17.062
♪ ♪

55:26.281 --> 55:28.282
[bell tinkles]

55:28.283 --> 55:29.783
[door creaks]

55:29.784 --> 55:31.076
- Good morning.

55:31.077 --> 55:32.786
- Ray.

55:32.787 --> 55:33.996
- You got a minute?

55:33.997 --> 55:35.289
- Yeah.

55:35.290 --> 55:36.540
What do you need?

55:36.541 --> 55:38.375
- I was wrong to hang up on you
the other night.

55:38.376 --> 55:40.252
I want to apologize.

55:41.671 --> 55:43.005
- Oh, forget it.

55:43.006 --> 55:44.131
No, you were right.

55:44.132 --> 55:46.383
I was all worked up
over nothing.

55:46.384 --> 55:49.261
- No, you were concerned,
and you were kind of right.

55:49.262 --> 55:50.471
See, Freddy...

55:50.472 --> 55:51.930
he was wanted.

55:51.931 --> 55:53.807
He dyed his hair.
He was wearing contact lenses.

55:53.808 --> 55:55.184
That's why you were confused.

55:55.185 --> 55:57.019
- [chuckles]

55:58.646 --> 55:59.772
Well, I'm just glad

55:59.773 --> 56:01.190
his old man's headed back
to prison.

56:01.191 --> 56:02.274
[tires screech]

56:02.275 --> 56:03.400
- Any day now.

56:03.401 --> 56:05.235
[Omar and The Howlers'
Dangerous Man playing]

56:05.236 --> 56:07.112
[energetic music]

56:07.113 --> 56:08.614
- I'm sure you're doing
everything you can.

56:08.615 --> 56:10.491
I appreciate that.

56:10.492 --> 56:13.327
Important thing is, he's not
a threat anymore, right?

56:13.328 --> 56:14.328
- ♪ Jump back, baby ♪

56:14.329 --> 56:16.121
♪ Keep your big mouth shut ♪

56:16.122 --> 56:17.414
♪ Don't say nothing ♪

56:17.415 --> 56:18.665
[bell tinkles]

56:18.666 --> 56:20.084
♪ You don't want to start ♪

56:20.085 --> 56:21.377
♪ To make me rant and rave ♪

56:21.378 --> 56:22.419
[bell tinkles]

56:22.420 --> 56:25.422
[music playing indistinctly]

56:27.509 --> 56:28.801
- Can I help you?

56:32.138 --> 56:34.306
- You think you could corral
this little filly

56:34.307 --> 56:35.933
in a frame for me?

56:37.018 --> 56:39.269
Kind of a rush job.

56:40.814 --> 56:42.731
It don't have to be too fancy.

56:42.732 --> 56:44.149
♪ ♪

56:44.150 --> 56:45.859
- You're busy, Rich.
I'll catch you.

56:45.860 --> 56:47.361
- All right.

56:49.322 --> 56:50.489
- ♪ You gonna draw back ♪

56:50.490 --> 56:51.990
♪ Start to scream and cry ♪

56:51.991 --> 56:54.034
[door thuds,
bells tinkle]

56:54.035 --> 56:55.702
- Sounds like old Ben's
got himself

56:55.703 --> 56:58.163
in a real shitstorm this time,

56:58.164 --> 57:01.166
and he's dragged you
right in there with him.

57:02.460 --> 57:04.044
- Who are you?

57:04.045 --> 57:06.880
- Name's Jim Bob Luke.

57:06.881 --> 57:08.006
Luke Detective Agency,

57:08.007 --> 57:10.467
Houston, Texas.

57:10.468 --> 57:12.719
[lively country music]

57:12.720 --> 57:14.555
- ♪ I've got the blues ♪

57:14.556 --> 57:16.348
[engine revving]

57:16.349 --> 57:17.891
♪ I've got the blues ♪

57:17.892 --> 57:20.185
- ♪ I've got the blues ♪

57:20.186 --> 57:23.856
- ♪ I ain't got nothing
but the blues ♪

57:23.857 --> 57:26.733
♪ I ain't got nothing
but the blues ♪

57:28.778 --> 57:31.655
- This one made it all the way
to the Houston paper.

57:31.656 --> 57:32.823
Front page.

57:32.824 --> 57:35.159
Mentions Freddy four times,

57:35.160 --> 57:37.244
just in case you missed it.

57:39.998 --> 57:42.249
This is six weeks ago.

57:42.250 --> 57:44.626
Buried on the back page.

57:44.627 --> 57:46.295
Mentions Freddy once.

57:47.464 --> 57:49.923
- So he turned
state evidence, then?

57:49.924 --> 57:51.383
- And your boy found himself

57:51.384 --> 57:53.260
on the ass end
of a federal case.

57:55.346 --> 57:58.891
Now, we know Freddy
ain't no saint,

57:58.892 --> 58:00.726
but if he's messing around
with these boys

58:00.727 --> 58:04.229
in the Dixie Mafia,
they some bad dudes.

58:04.230 --> 58:06.023
How far do you want
to take this, Ben?

58:14.365 --> 58:15.741
- [chuckles]

58:15.742 --> 58:17.701
If he's alive,
I want to see him.

58:17.702 --> 58:18.785
- All right.

58:18.786 --> 58:21.413
Well, I got some hunches
on that.

58:21.414 --> 58:23.916
I want to feel them out first.

58:23.917 --> 58:26.793
But first thing,
we got to relocate.

58:26.794 --> 58:30.088
If Price is as slick
as his mustache,

58:30.089 --> 58:32.966
we got to get the old hoss here
out of the county.

58:35.303 --> 58:36.678
- What do I do?

58:36.679 --> 58:40.265
- For now, just go home,
you know, act dumb.

58:40.266 --> 58:41.475
Let me do some legwork,

58:41.476 --> 58:43.644
and when I get Russel
settled somewhere,

58:43.645 --> 58:45.771
I'll... I'll give you a call.

58:48.233 --> 58:50.609
[indistinct chatter on TV]

58:50.610 --> 58:52.653
- Hey, thanks.
Thanks.

58:52.654 --> 58:54.821
Over here.

58:54.822 --> 58:56.490
- Wanted to buy you a drink,
partner,

58:56.491 --> 58:58.158
for bringing Holly back
in one piece.

58:58.159 --> 58:59.284
- Yeah.

58:59.285 --> 59:00.702
- Last time,
he blacked her eye.

59:00.703 --> 59:02.204
Someday,
someone's gonna settle...

59:02.205 --> 59:04.331
- [sighs]

59:04.332 --> 59:05.999
- I'd like to do it myself.

59:06.000 --> 59:07.751
[telephones ring]

59:07.752 --> 59:09.336
- At one time,
a Singapore Sling

59:09.337 --> 59:10.629
would have been
the only answer.

59:10.630 --> 59:13.632
[pensive music]

59:13.633 --> 59:21.640
♪ ♪

59:27.355 --> 59:30.148
- ♪ Let's all go
to the lobby ♪

59:30.149 --> 59:31.608
♪ Let's all go to the lobby ♪

59:31.609 --> 59:33.151
[indistinct conversations]

59:33.152 --> 59:35.612
♪ Let's all go to the lobby ♪

59:35.613 --> 59:36.947
♪ To get ourselves a drink ♪

59:36.948 --> 59:38.365
- What?
No, no, no, no.

59:38.366 --> 59:40.617
Say that again.
You broke up.

59:41.703 --> 59:43.370
I-I can't...

59:43.371 --> 59:45.372
No, I'm...
I'm catching every third word.

59:45.373 --> 59:46.540
Say it again.

59:46.541 --> 59:48.041
- Here you go.

59:48.042 --> 59:49.751
- ♪ Chocolate bars
and the candy ♪

59:49.752 --> 59:52.004
♪ So let's all go
to the lobby ♪

59:52.005 --> 59:54.006
- All right, thanks.

59:54.007 --> 59:55.424
[sighs]

59:55.425 --> 59:57.301
[grunts]

59:57.302 --> 59:58.510
- What'd you find out?

59:58.511 --> 01:00:00.512
- Well,
I made a bunch of calls.

01:00:00.513 --> 01:00:02.889
I got this gal
I used to run with.

01:00:02.890 --> 01:00:05.934
She works in the office
of the FBI.

01:00:05.935 --> 01:00:07.728
It seems Freddy

01:00:07.729 --> 01:00:10.689
is assigned to
the witness relocation program.

01:00:10.690 --> 01:00:11.982
You know what that is?

01:00:11.983 --> 01:00:15.527
- They give people a new start,
new name, new place...

01:00:15.528 --> 01:00:16.737
mob informers and shit.

01:00:16.738 --> 01:00:19.740
- Yeah, you got the picture,
framer.

01:00:19.741 --> 01:00:21.992
They're the ones
that set you up.

01:00:21.993 --> 01:00:24.077
So over the last couple years,

01:00:24.078 --> 01:00:26.455
your son's been running
with the Dixie boys,

01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:29.875
doing whatever Mafia types do.

01:00:29.876 --> 01:00:32.377
And the shit gets
way over Freddy's head,

01:00:32.378 --> 01:00:35.130
and the law
comes down on him hard.

01:00:35.131 --> 01:00:37.090
So to keep from going
to the slammer,

01:00:37.091 --> 01:00:39.051
he starts to sing
like a little bird

01:00:39.052 --> 01:00:42.179
against his old buddies,
the Dixie boys.

01:00:42.180 --> 01:00:45.724
Now, you don't want to fuck
with the Dixie Mafia.

01:00:45.725 --> 01:00:49.478
And the feds know that,
so they make Freddy a deal.

01:00:49.479 --> 01:00:52.022
They'll hide him
if he gives them what they need.

01:00:52.023 --> 01:00:54.066
- So they faked it.

01:00:54.067 --> 01:00:55.942
- It's beautiful.

01:00:55.943 --> 01:00:59.321
If the Dixie Mafia believes
that Freddy is dead, well...

01:00:59.322 --> 01:01:00.656
[chuckles]

01:01:00.657 --> 01:01:03.283
What's the use of gunning
for a dead guy, right?

01:01:03.284 --> 01:01:05.327
Good plan,
don't you think?

01:01:05.328 --> 01:01:06.662
[chuckles]

01:01:07.872 --> 01:01:09.247
- Then who's in that grave?

01:01:09.248 --> 01:01:11.083
- Yeah, and where's my son?

01:01:13.336 --> 01:01:15.629
- Well, that's a good one.

01:01:15.630 --> 01:01:16.672
[clicks tongue]

01:01:16.673 --> 01:01:17.714
[cell phone ringing]

01:01:17.715 --> 01:01:18.965
Oh!

01:01:18.966 --> 01:01:20.467
That would be for me.

01:01:20.468 --> 01:01:22.052
These things are amazing.

01:01:22.053 --> 01:01:23.261
You seen these?

01:01:23.262 --> 01:01:24.888
Ah, fuck, you've been
in prison forever.

01:01:24.889 --> 01:01:25.972
Jim Bob.

01:01:25.973 --> 01:01:28.016
You're breaking up.
Hold on.

01:01:30.937 --> 01:01:33.105
Okay, that's better.
Go ahead.

01:01:33.106 --> 01:01:34.773
- You should really
be scared...

01:01:34.774 --> 01:01:38.110
- [sighs]
I need another beer.

01:01:38.111 --> 01:01:39.486
[grunts]

01:01:39.487 --> 01:01:42.489
[indistinct chatter]

01:01:45.118 --> 01:01:47.744
- Well, if it ain't
Josey Wales.

01:01:47.745 --> 01:01:51.623
Hey, kill any banditos lately,
cowboy?

01:01:51.624 --> 01:01:53.750
- Jack, you're drunk.
Leave me alone.

01:01:53.751 --> 01:01:55.585
- Ah, let me buy you a drink.

01:01:55.586 --> 01:01:57.963
And you can tell me
about how you...

01:01:57.964 --> 01:01:59.214
- I don't want your drink,
Jack,

01:01:59.215 --> 01:02:00.549
and I don't want your company.

01:02:00.550 --> 01:02:03.552
- Let me tell you something,
Mr. Dane...

01:02:03.553 --> 01:02:05.303
Ahh!
Oh, God!

01:02:05.304 --> 01:02:06.388
[groans]

01:02:06.389 --> 01:02:07.639
- Hurts, doesn't it?

01:02:07.640 --> 01:02:10.225
- [groaning]

01:02:10.226 --> 01:02:12.185
- Hey.
Hey. Let him go.

01:02:12.186 --> 01:02:13.311
It's not a good idea.

01:02:13.312 --> 01:02:17.149
- [groaning]

01:02:20.445 --> 01:02:23.155
- [sighs]

01:02:23.156 --> 01:02:25.282
You didn't have to do that.

01:02:27.785 --> 01:02:30.370
- Well, I didn't want to see you
damage the fella.

01:02:30.371 --> 01:02:31.371
[sniffs]

01:02:31.372 --> 01:02:33.206
Can we get three beers?

01:02:33.207 --> 01:02:34.291
- [chuckles]

01:02:35.585 --> 01:02:37.127
- In Washington,

01:02:37.128 --> 01:02:40.881
it has been established that
persons who have recently died

01:02:40.882 --> 01:02:45.635
have been returning to life
and committing acts of murder.

01:02:45.636 --> 01:02:48.638
Widespread investigation
of morgues and funeral homes...

01:02:48.639 --> 01:02:51.141
- Hoss, if you want to see
your boy,

01:02:51.142 --> 01:02:53.810
we got to move.

01:02:53.811 --> 01:02:55.228
You can stay at my place.

01:02:55.229 --> 01:02:57.189
- Human victims...

01:02:57.190 --> 01:02:59.941
- Y'all are leaving?

01:02:59.942 --> 01:03:01.526
- This whole operation's
being run

01:03:01.527 --> 01:03:04.070
out of the Houston office.

01:03:04.071 --> 01:03:06.615
That's my hood.

